						               													<description>The game is set in Thessaloniki at the end of the 13th Century until the beginning of the 14th century. We witness one of the most grand flee markets of the Byzantine Empire, the &amp;quot;Dimitria&amp;quot;. The grand flee markets of the time had significant value, similar to today's exhibitions. Such markets consisted of tradesman, bankers, musicians, actors and magicians. Nicolo Beltram a great tradesman from Genova, has to visit a banker to convert some byzantine coins (that slowly lose their value) to Genevese coins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game board consists of 2 round circuits on which players move based on dice rolls. Except for moving along the board, picking up power or money cards, players can interact with merchants placed along the board, as well as interact with other players but only when both players end up on the same tile. Each player then rolls a die and multiplies it with each current power status and the one with the least takes damage on his/her power status.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As the goal of the game players by selling and buying products to gain the most power and money.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
